<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-08-23T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-08-23T16:00:00-05:00" n="330" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d330">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">123C11/337: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Welles</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-08-23T16:00:00-05:00">August 23, 1933—4
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 4:33 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>181. The President of the Republic this morning informed me that the
                                appointment of Caffery as my successor here would be most acceptable
                                to the Cuban Government.<note n="38" xml:id="d330fn38">It appears
                                    that this agrément was requested by the Acting Secretary of
                                    State over the telephone on August 22.</note></p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>